    content: "# Ancient Products Guide\n\n# Ancient Products — Setup Instructions\n\n**Applies to:** All Ancient products.\n\n> **Note:** The Ancient Spoofer is detected on most games.\n\n## Loader Download\n\nThe loader for Ancient: http://undetect.net/download/loader\n\n## Windows Version Compatibility\n\nCompatible with Windows 10, Windows 11 (21H2, 22H2, 23H2, 24h2, 25H2)\n\n## Additional Info\n\nBuilt in Hwid Spoofer: Included\n\n## Pre-Setup Requirements\n\n**Disable PC PIN password and BitLocker BEFORE using Ancient products.** Disabling TPM and Hyper-V with new Windows builds can cause issues getting back into your PC with a PIN enabled.\n\n\n## PRE-INJECTION SETUP (REQUIRED)\nBefore launching the loader, complete ALL steps below:\n\n❌ Disable Windows Real-Time Protection\n\n❌ Disable Windows Defender (use Sordum DControl)\n\n❌ Uninstall ALL antivirus software (not just disable)\n\n❌ Disable ALL startup apps\n\n❌ Disable Exploit Protection\n\n❌ Disable any overlays other than the one you are using for this product.\n\n🔄 Restart your PC after doing any of the above steps\n\n❌ Completely Uninstall:\n- Faceit\n- Vanguard\n\n# OVERLAY SETUP (CHOOSE ONE)\n IMPORTANT:\nThe cheat does NOT support fullscreen exclusive\nYou must use:\n- Windowed\n- Borderless\n- Fullscreen (Windowed)\n\n## Option 1: Discord Overlay\n- Open Discord Settings\n- Go to Game Overlay\n- Enable overlay\n- Disable Legacy Overlay\n\nFix:\nIf you see “No suitable overlay”:\n\nTurn overlay OFF → ON again\n\n## Option 2: Medal Overlay\n- Download: https://medal.tv/download\n- Create an account and install overlay\n\n⚠️ Users in Russia will need a VPN to download this\n\nINJECTING THE CHEAT\nLaunch the loader:\nhttp://undetect.net/download/loader\n\nIf it doesn’t load/download → use a VPN\n\nEnter your key\n\nPress Inject\n\n AFTER INJECTION\nThe loader will close automatically\n→ This is NORMAL\n\nLaunch your game\n\nOpen the menu with:\nINSERT key\n\n FINAL NOTES\nIf ANY step above is skipped → it will not work\n\nMost issues come from:\n\nHyper-V not fully disabled\n\nAntivirus still active\n\nWrong BIOS settings\n\n\n---\n\n### If PC Reboots 2–3 Times in a Row\n\nOpen CMD as administrator and enter:\n```\nbcdedit /set hypervisorlaunchtype auto\n```\n\n---\n\n## Common Errors and Fixes\n\n### \"Please launch SteelSeries moment overlay\" (for NVIDIA/GeForce)\n\nDisable and re-enable the GeForce overlay.\n\n### \"Please launch SteelSeries Sonar overlay\" (for SteelSeries)\n\nPress the Sonar bind before launching so the overlay activates.\n\n### Flickering Menus or Black Screens In-Game\n\nOpen SteelSeries → Settings → Moments → Capture and Sound → Turn off \"Allow Moments to Capture While Gaming\".\n\n### \"Please disable Intel Rapid Storage Technology\"\n\nRST must be disabled. Instructions: https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/all/uninstalling-the-intelr-rapid-storage-technology/e3c4b6d6-56ba-4ac5-be50-89843c9d9b22\n\n### Bind Button Does Not Work\n\nReinject. If that doesn't help, run the overlay as administrator.\n\n### No Menu Appears or Loader Closes Immediately\n\nInstall the library from: https://aka.ms/vs/17/release/vc_redist.x64.exe\n\n### \"Unsupported Firmware\"\n\nConvert the disk to GPT and the BIOS to UEFI.\n\n### Error 0x296\n\nReinject.\n\n### \"Unknown network error\"\n\nProblem with your internet connection. Check your connection and try again. If using VPN, try disabling it.\n\n### \"Failed to allocate memory / to map memory — Please reboot pc and try again\"\n\nThe driver was installed incorrectly. Reboot and try again. If in an internet cafe and the error recurs, try another PC. If it doesn't help, clean autorun programs. Download Autoruns (https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/autoruns) and disable non-system startup programs. In some cases, drivers for deleted programs may remain in the system.\n\n### \"Failed to load dependencies — Make sure all antiviruses are disabled\"\n\nTurn off all protection and remove all anti-cheats and antiviruses from your PC. If it doesn't help, clean autorun programs.\n\n### \"Please uninstall Vanguard/Faceit first\"\n\nUninstall Vanguard/FaceIT anti-cheat from your PC.\n\n### \"AES instruction set is not supported\"\n\nThe processor does not support AES instruction set. This cannot be fixed.\n\n### \"Please enable Intel VT-X/AMD-V in the BIOS\"\n\nEnter BIOS and search for \"Intel Virtualization Technology\" / \"Intel VT-X\" / \"AMD-V\" / \"SVM mode\" and enable it.\n\n### \"VMX/SVM is not supported\"\n\nGo to Control Panel → Programs → Enable or Disable Windows Features and ensure \"Virtual Machine Platform\" and \"Hyper-V\" are disabled.\n\nIf the error persists, open CMD as administrator:\n```\nbcdedit /set hypervisorlaunchtype off\n```\nThen restart.\n\nFor Windows 11 users, if previous methods didn't help, run PowerShell as administrator and insert commands listed below one by one:\n```\ntakeown /F \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvix64.exe\"\nicacls \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvix64.exe\" /grant *$(([System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).User.Value):F\ntakeown /F \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvax64.exe\"\nicacls \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvax64.exe\" /grant *$(([System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()).User.Value):F\ndel \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvix64.exe\"\ndel \"C:\\Windows\\System32\\hvax64.exe\"\n```\n\n### \"Either virtual or RAID disk is present\"\n\nTurn off the spoofer or turn off RAID in BIOS settings with a complete reinstallation of Windows.\n\n### \"Unsupported firmware\"\n\nConvert the OS disk to GPT format using the mbr2gpt tool built into Windows or another disk management utility. Switch BIOS from Legacy mode to UEFI mode.\n\n### \"CRD failed at XXX / Failed to init render\"\n\nFor desktop PCs: the graphics card is old and unsupported. For laptops: disable the built-in graphics card in BIOS.\n\n### \"Incorrect HWID\"\n\nOpen CMD as administrator and run these commands:\n```\nwmic diskdrive get Caption, SerialNumber\nwmic baseboard get SerialNumber\n```\nIf any command fails with an error, something is wrong with your PC. Try reinstalling Windows.\n\n### Specific Requirements for Ancient cod and Ancient Battlefield 6\n\nSVM [AMD] / VT-X [INTEL] (BIOS) enabled.\n16GB RAM (or more).\nHyper V disabled for AMD CPU only.\nSecure Boot enabled.",
