    content: "# Predator CS2 Guide\n\n1.Go to https://predator.systems/products/ and Register an account\n\n2.Activate your key\n\n3.Obtain Loader here https://predator.systems/panel/subscriptions\n\nWe highly recommend you to follow these steps if you are experiencing troubles with launching our software:\n🚨 Pre-Launch Setup Guide 🚨\n\nTo ensure a smooth experience, follow these steps:\n\nDisable Antivirus\n\nTemporarily disable your antivirus software. If necessary, uninstall it completely.\n\nDisable Microsoft Defender\n\nTurn off Microsoft Defender to avoid conflicts.\n\nDisable Driver Anti-Cheats\n\nFor Faceit: Open CMD as an admin and type:\n\n\nCopy\narduinoCopyEditsc stop faceit\nFor Valorant: Open CMD as an admin and type the following:\n\n\nCopy\narduinoCopyEditsc stop vgc\nsc stop vgk\nAvoid Using \"-vulcan\" Launch Option\n\nImportant: Do not use the “-vulcan” launch option. It is not supported.\n\nSynchronize Windows Time Settings\n\nEnsure your Windows time settings are properly synchronized to avoid any issues.\n\n⚠️ Troubleshooting Guide ⚠️\n\nProblem: \"An error occurred in the secure channel support\" / \"The request has timed out\" / \"The operation timed out\"\nSolution:\nTraffic may be blocked by something like Anti-cheat, Anti-virus, Firewall, or your Internet provider.\n\nFully uninstall your antivirus and other anti-cheat software. Simply disabling them might not be enough.\n\nResync your time and region in Windows settings.\n\nTry enabling/disabling VPN as this can sometimes resolve the issue.\n\nProblem: \"Internal public server error\"\nSolution:\nTraffic is being blocked by something like Anti-cheat, Anti-virus, Firewall, or your Internet provider.\n\nFully uninstall your antivirus and other anti-cheat software, as disabling them might not be enough.\n\nProblem: \"Antivirus Interference detected\"\nSolution:\nTraffic is being blocked by something like Anti-cheat, Anti-virus, or Malware.\n\nFully uninstall your antivirus and anti-cheat software, as disabling them isn’t always sufficient.\n\nScan your PC with antivirus tools to ensure that your system isn’t infected.\n\nProblem: Reason: [<code>] sym: <some info>\nSolution:\n\nCreate a ticket in Discord and provide a screenshot of this information.\n\nTo capture the necessary details, press WIN + R, type “winver”, and share the information.\n\nProblem: Reason: modules::load_module: failed to create section\nSolution:\n\nFully uninstall your antivirus and other anti-cheat software, as disabling them might not be sufficient.\n\nBy following these solutions, you should be able to resolve the most common issues quickly! 💡",
